				<li id="16731914" class="cmnt-root" data="14" data-d="1657165631000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578097/Ghiza's-Wheel" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">06 Jul 2022 23:47</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16731914" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">I don&apos;t know why I never see it mentioned anywhere but this thing one handed is the way to go, specifically with the heavy attacks. 2-handed the heavy attack does a swing that leaves the blade spinning behind you, but one handed will swing the blade over and infront of you, leaving it in the place where it lands to continue doing damage with the saw. <br/><br/>I&apos;m currently using this with the pulley crossbow offhand, and after reading the lore of Ghiza, the weapons, and the locations of the weapons i think the game even tries to hint you towards this with the weapons relatively low str requirement (for a colossal anyway).<br/><br/>Combine the 1 handed heavies with some charged damage increases like Axe Talisman and Spiked Crystal Tear, then some stacking damage bonuses like Millicent&apos;s Prosthesis and Rotten Winged Sword Insignia as well as the Thorny Cracked Tear, then put white mask on and Lord of Blood&apos;s Exultation and watch those heavy attack numbers go up and up and up and up!</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16731914" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share